===Noun===
{{en-noun|~}}

# {{lb|en|US|Canada}} A flavoured [[beverage]] consisting of water, lemon, and [[sweetener]], sometimes ice, served mainly as a [[refreshment]].
# {{lb|en|UK|AU|NZ}} A clear, [[carbonated]] [[beverage]] made from lemon or artificial lemon flavouring, water, and sugar.

====Usage notes====
In locations where the meaning as a carbonated beverage is common, the still beverage is often called "homemade lemonade" or "old-fashioned lemonade". The terms "lemon(-flavored) drink" and "lemon(-flavored) beverage" generally denote any lemon-flavored drink.

